Mulish ExtraLight Regular (Mulish-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Mulish ExtraLight'.

Pass

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mulish ExtraLight Italic (Mulish-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Mulish ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mulish Light Regular (Mulish-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'Mulish-Light', Everything looks good.

Mulish Light Regular (Mulish-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Mulish Light'.

Mulish Light Italic (Mulish-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Mulish Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-Regular', Everything looks good.

Mulish SemiBold Regular (Mulish-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mulish SemiBold Regular (Mulish-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mulish SemiBold Regular (Mulish-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Mulish SemiBold'.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Mulish SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'Mulish-Bold', Everything looks good.

Mulish Bold Italic (Mulish-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mulish ExtraBold Regular (Mulish-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Mulish ExtraBold Regular (Mulish-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Mulish ExtraBold Regular (Mulish-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Mulish ExtraBold'.

Pass

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mulish-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mulish ExtraBold Italic (Mulish-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Mulish ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mulish Black Regular (Mulish-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Mulish Black'.

License text

Cannot check license text because of unkown entity 'Vernon Adams' (NID8). Please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
This Font Software is licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1. This license is available with a FAQ at: http://scripts.sil.org/OFL
, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Mulish Black Italic (Mulish-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mulish' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Mulish Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass
